ns can become clear to those who do not understand them yet.<br>
<br>
The  'you haven't earned it' agrument also seems a bit fuzzy to me.  Do you actually tell any members of your own guild 'Sorry,  you haven't earned it yet,  so you can't attend this flagging.'?  Maybe I'm wrong.   Maybe you have a rule that someone must be a member for a year before they can attend these flaggings.  Maybe you have a rule that if any of your members move to a smaller guild they must destroy any VT loot they have as the smaller guild is not capable of doing VT.  I doubt if you have these rules, but to be consistent with your arguments you should.<br>
