What I am starting to see funny about this whole deal is this...<br>
<br>
It doesn't matter to me who has already passed these flag mobs or who hasn't...<br>
<br>
If these flag mobs go on rotation every guild that has done the flag mob won't need to be put on the rotation because they've already passed the test to get their flags so there would be no need for them to be on it.  Plus... Those guilds who pass the flag test to go to the next tier and get put on the rotation for these mobs will autopass every single time because they also won't need to redo the tests.<br>
<br>
My reasoning... As has been stated by Verant... if you have a raiding force of 32 inside these 3rd tier or higher zones, you can have players not yet flagged also enter these zones as long as they do not leave the raid.  If they leave the raid they autozoneout after 3 minutes.  Thus no need for raiding forces inside these zones to do said mobs over again... BoTS, FK, TL, NB, ED do not need to go onto the rotation as they have their flags and guildmates won't need them that don't have them unless they start to get a large number of members who need the flags.  Then they'd probably set up a date for one large raid on those flag mobs instead of doing them a bit here and a bit there.  Guilds like LoM, CB, SoTE, EoTF will all autopass once they get their flags and go onto the rotation.<br>
<br>
More questions... will they even request to be put onto the rotation after defeating said mobs?  What would be the reasoning to do so? *giggle*<br>
<br>
Strange reasoning to put PoP flag mobs onto the Rotation when noone will care to be on it.<br>
<br>
I can see the future... can you??  Guild S, Guild X, Guild Y, Guild Z and Guild A are on the &quot;rotation&quot; for Behemoth....  They have their flags so they are all on autopass... Guild S is up for the next kill (just for spite to say who's turn it is), Guild Y has 10 people that they want to have Flags so as to avoid the 3 minute rule about non flagged raiding members and decide to plan a date to take down Behemoth.  Since all guilds on the &quot;rotation&quot; are on autopass, noone will care when Guild Y decides to go take down Behemoth and take their kill out of Rotation and cause a major hassle about killing out of turn because it's always up.<br>
<br>
Doesn't this contradict what the Rotation system is about?  Isn't the Rotation system about giving each guild/alliance a chance at specific mobs at certain times when they get onto the rotation of these specific mobs?  Giving each guild/alliance an opportunity to take down certain mobs for equipment/questpieces?...<br>
<br>
&quot;Nyca, put Guild F on the rotation for Behemoth... Behemoth down at suchandsuchatime at suchandsuchadate... oh and btw, put us on autopass too we don't need him for a while...&quot;<br>
<br>
Certain Guildleaders have already stated here that they don't have much incentive to do these mobs anymore anyway as they have gotten what they need.  Seems more like what some people have posted in one way or another... That they prefer their peace and serenity of non busy zones... no trains, no morons, no fights over camps.<br>
